reviews.subject: Physics 101
reviews.review: Dr. Carter explains complex concepts very clearly. Her lectures are engaging and the problem sets are challenging but fair.

reviews.subject: Calculus II
reviews.review: Prof. Smith is very knowledgeable and patient. The exams are tough but manageable if you follow along in class.

reviews.subject: Introduction to Philosophy
reviews.review: Dr. Lee's lectures can be a bit dry, but she is always open to questions and provides good feedback on essays.

reviews.subject: Computer Science 101
reviews.review: Prof. Brown is difficult to understand and his assignments are poorly explained. The grading is harsh.

reviews.subject: Organic Chemistry
reviews.review: Dr. Wilson is an excellent professor who really cares about her students. Her exams are challenging but fair.

reviews.subject: World History
reviews.review: Prof. Johnson's passion for history is contagious. His lectures are always interesting and he encourages class participation.

reviews.subject: Psychology 101
reviews.review: Dr. Taylor is knowledgeable, but her lectures can be monotonous. The material is interesting, though.

reviews.subject: Microeconomics
reviews.review: Prof. Anderson's lectures are difficult to follow and the textbook doesn't help much. The exams are tricky.

reviews.subject: Biology 201
reviews.review: Dr. Harris is very enthusiastic about the subject. Her lab sessions are well-organized and informative.

reviews.subject: Introduction to Sociology
reviews.review: Prof. Martinez is one of the best professors I've had. His classes are thought-provoking and he really cares about his students.

reviews.subject: English Literature
reviews.review: Dr. Thompson is very knowledgeable, but her grading can be harsh. She expects a lot from her students.

reviews.subject: Statistics
reviews.review: Prof. Evans makes statistics interesting and understandable. His exams are tough but fair if you study.

reviews.subject: Environmental Science
reviews.review: Dr. Davis is a fantastic professor who is passionate about the environment. Her lectures are always engaging.

reviews.subject: Marketing 101
reviews.review: Prof. White's lectures are not very engaging and the assignments are confusing. The grading is inconsistent.

reviews.subject: Anatomy and Physiology
reviews.review: Dr. Rodriguez is a great professor. She explains difficult concepts well and her exams are challenging but fair.

reviews.subject: Political Science
reviews.review: Prof. Walker's lectures are informative, but he can be a bit dry. The material is interesting, though.

reviews.subject: Chemistry 101
reviews.review: Dr. King is an amazing professor who makes chemistry fun. Her labs are well-organized and her lectures are clear.

reviews.subject: Introduction to Art History
reviews.review: Prof. Harris is knowledgeable, but his lectures can be a bit boring. The material is interesting, though.

reviews.subject: Human Anatomy
reviews.review: Dr. Miller is very thorough and makes sure everyone understands the material. Her exams are tough but fair.

reviews.subject: Physics 201
reviews.review: Prof. Scott's lectures are difficult to follow and his exams are very challenging. The grading is harsh.
